## 🧠 SKILLS & ECOSYSTEM

> **First-time setup: scan the project, detect every skill in use, then assemble the ecosystem.
> Each skill contributes structure, conventions, security rules, dependencies, and tooling.
> The sum of all active skills defines the complete project configuration.**

### How skill detection works

1. **Read config files** — package.json, pyproject.toml, go.mod, Cargo.toml, Gemfile, composer.json, requirements.txt, CMakeLists.txt, etc.
2. **Identify every skill present** using the detection heuristics below.
3. **Load each skill's contribution** to STRUCTURE MAP, CONVENTIONS, TECH STACK, and all other sections.
4. **Merge overlapping rules** — if two skills define a `controllers/` folder, merge their rules.
5. **Present the assembled ecosystem** to the user and confirm before proceeding.

### Skills manifest

> _Each skill defines: what it detects, what structure it adds, conventions, security rules, and ecosystem defaults.
> Skills are designed to compose — multiple skills can be active in one project._

| Skill | Detected by | Adds structure | Adds conventions | Adds security |
|-------|------------|---------------|-----------------|--------------|
| **node-express** | `package.json` has `express` dependency | `src/controllers/`, `src/models/`, `src/routes/`, `src/middleware/`, `src/services/` | camelCase files, MVC pattern, async/await, error middleware | JWT middleware, helmet, CORS, rate limiting |
| **node-nest** | `package.json` has `@nestjs/core` | `src/modules/`, `src/modules/*/controller.ts`, `src/modules/*/service.ts`, `src/modules/*/module.ts` | PascalCase files, decorator pattern, DTOs, modules | Guards, pipes, interceptors, JWT auth module |
| **react** | `package.json` has `react` | `src/components/`, `src/hooks/`, `src/pages/`, `src/context/`, `src/utils/` | PascalCase components, co-located CSS modules, custom hooks | Input sanitization, XSS prevention, CSP headers |
| **react-native** | `package.json` has `react-native` | `src/screens/`, `src/navigation/`, `src/components/`, `src/hooks/`, `android/`, `ios/` | PascalCase screens, platform-specific files (`.ios.tsx`, `.android.tsx`) | Secure storage, certificate pinning, deep link validation |
| **next** | `package.json` has `next` | `app/` or `pages/`, `app/api/`, `components/`, `lib/`, `public/` | File-based routing, server/client components, RSC conventions | Server actions validation, middleware auth, API route protection |
| **vue** | `package.json` has `vue` | `src/components/`, `src/views/`, `src/store/`, `src/router/`, `src/composables/` | PascalCase SFCs, composables, pinia stores, vue-router | Route guards, input sanitization, CSP |
| **angular** | `package.json` has `@angular/core` | `src/app/modules/`, `src/app/components/`, `src/app/services/`, `src/app/guards/` | PascalCase classes, service DI pattern, NgModules, standalone | Auth guards, HTTP interceptors, XSS sanitization |
| **django** | `requirements.txt` or `Pipfile` has `django` | `project/`, `apps/*/models.py`, `apps/*/views.py`, `apps/*/urls.py`, `apps/*/serializers.py` | snake_case files, Django REST pattern, model inheritance | CSRF, XSS, SQL injection (ORM), permission classes |
| **fastapi** | `requirements.txt` or `pyproject.toml` has `fastapi` | `app/`, `app/api/`, `app/models/`, `app/schemas/`, `app/core/`, `app/db/` | snake_case files, Pydantic schemas, dependency injection | OAuth2 middleware, CORS, input validation via Pydantic |
| **flask** | `requirements.txt` or `Pipfile` has `flask` | `app/`, `app/routes/`, `app/models/`, `app/templates/`, `app/static/` | snake_case files, Flask blueprints, app factory pattern | Flask-Login, CSRFProtect, SQL injection prevention |
| **spring-boot** | `pom.xml` or `build.gradle` has `spring-boot` | `src/main/java/../controller/`, `service/`, `repository/`, `model/`, `config/`, `security/` | PascalCase classes, annotation-driven config, layered architecture | Spring Security, method-level security, OAuth2 resource server |
| **go** | `go.mod` present | `cmd/`, `internal/`, `pkg/`, `api/`, `migrations/` | snake_case files, Go package conventions, interface-based DI | JWT middleware, TLS config, SQL injection prevention |
| **rust** | `Cargo.toml` present | `src/main.rs`, `src/lib.rs`, `src/bin/`, `src/modules/`, `tests/`, `benches/` | snake_case files, module per concern, Result/Option pattern | Memory safety via ownership, secure crypto via `ring` |
| **php-laravel** | `composer.json` has `laravel/framework` | `app/Http/Controllers/`, `app/Models/`, `app/Http/Middleware/`, `routes/`, `database/migrations/` | PascalCase controllers, Eloquent models, artisan commands | CSRF, XSS, Eloquent SQL injection protection, auth gates |
| **ruby-rails** | `Gemfile` has `rails` | `app/controllers/`, `app/models/`, `app/views/`, `config/routes.rb`, `db/migrate/` | snake_case files, Rails conventions, RESTful resources | CSRF token, SQL injection via ActiveRecord, strong params |
| **flutter** | `pubspec.yaml` has `flutter` | `lib/`, `lib/screens/`, `lib/widgets/`, `lib/models/`, `lib/services/`, `lib/providers/` | PascalCase widgets, Dart conventions, BLoC/Provider pattern | Secure storage, certificate pinning, input validation |
| **svelte** | `package.json` has `svelte` | `src/lib/`, `src/routes/`, `src/components/`, `src/stores/` | PascalCase components, SvelteKit file-based routing, stores | Input sanitization, CSP, server-side validation |
| **graphql** | `package.json` or `requirements.txt` has `graphql` | `src/graphql/schemas/`, `src/graphql/resolvers/`, `src/graphql/mutations/` | GraphQL SDL, resolver pattern, dataloader batching | Query depth limiting, auth directives, field-level permissions |
| **docker** | `Dockerfile` or `docker-compose.yml` present | `Dockerfile`, `.dockerignore`, `docker-compose.yml`, `docker/` | Multi-stage builds, compose services, health checks | No secrets in images, non-root user, image scanning |
| **kubernetes** | `k8s/` or `deploy/` has YAML manifests | `k8s/`, `k8s/base/`, `k8s/overlays/`, `helm/` | Kustomize or Helm chart structure, namespaced resources | Network policies, pod security contexts, secrets via External Secrets |
| **database-postgres** | Config, `package.json` or `requirements.txt` has `pg`/`psycopg2`/`postgres` | `migrations/`, `seeds/`, `db/` | SQL migration files, seed scripts, connection pooling | Parameterized queries only, connection encryption, row-level security |
| **database-mongo** | Config, `package.json` or `requirements.txt` has `mongoose`/`mongodb`/`pymongo` | `src/models/`, `migrations/`, `seeds/` | Mongoose/MongoEngine schemas, aggregation pipelines | Input sanitization, NoSQL injection prevention, field-level encryption |
| **database-prisma** | `package.json` or `schema.prisma` has `prisma` | `prisma/schema.prisma`, `prisma/migrations/`, `src/repositories/` | Prisma schema, repository pattern, migration workflow | Parameterized queries, row-level access, field encryption |
| **database-redis** | Config or dependency file has `redis` | `src/cache/`, `src/queues/` | Redis connection pooling, cache key conventions | TLS for Redis, auth token, key prefixing |
| **testing-cypress** | `package.json` has `cypress` | `cypress/e2e/`, `cypress/fixtures/`, `cypress/support/` | Page object model, custom commands, fixture-driven tests | Test isolation, no real auth tokens in fixtures |
| **testing-playwright** | `package.json` has `@playwright/test` | `e2e/`, `e2e/fixtures/`, `e2e/pages/` | Page object model, test fixtures, parallel execution | Test isolation, no real auth tokens |
| **testing-vitest** | `package.json` has `vitest` | `src/__tests__/`, `src/__mocks__/` | In-source testing, mock factory pattern, coverage thresholds | No secrets in tests, isolated test DB |
| **testing-jest** | `package.json` has `jest` | `tests/unit/`, `tests/__mocks__/` | `[name].test.js` mirroring src structure, mock factories | No secrets in tests, isolated test DB |
| **testing-pytest** | `requirements.txt` or `pyproject.toml` has `pytest` | `tests/`, `tests/conftest.py`, `tests/fixtures/` | Function-based tests, conftest fixtures, parametrize | No secrets in tests, isolated test DB |
| **ci-github** | `.github/workflows/` has YAML files | `.github/workflows/`, `.github/actions/` | CI/CD pipeline conventions, reusable workflows | No secrets in logs, OIDC for cloud auth |
| **ci-gitlab** | `.gitlab-ci.yml` present | `.gitlab-ci.yml`, `.gitlab/` | CI/CD stages, caching, artifact conventions | No secrets in logs, protected variables |
| **mobile-ios** | `*.xcodeproj` or `Package.swift` has iOS config | `Sources/`, `Sources/Models/`, `Sources/Views/`, `Sources/Controllers/`, `Sources/Services/` | Swift conventions, MVVM pattern, SwiftUI/UIKit separation | Keychain storage, certificate pinning, app transport security |
| **mobile-android** | `build.gradle` or `build.gradle.kts` present | `app/src/main/java/`, `res/`, `app/src/main/res/` | Kotlin conventions, MVVM with ViewModel, Jetpack Compose or XML | Encrypted shared prefs, certificate pinning, runtime permissions |
| **terraform** | `*.tf` files present | `terraform/`, `terraform/environments/`, `terraform/modules/` | HCL conventions, module structure, remote state | No secrets in state, IAM least privilege, remote state encryption |
| **python** | `requirements.txt`, `setup.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or `Pipfile` present | `src/`, `src/models/`, `src/services/`, `src/utils/`, `notebooks/` | snake_case, type hints, virtual env, entry point | Input validation, dependency auditing, env var isolation |
| **cli** | `package.json` has `bin` or `argparse`/`click`/`commander` in deps | `bin/`, `src/commands/`, `src/utils/` | CLI-specific conventions, subcommand pattern, help text | Input validation, no secrets in output, safe subprocess calls |

### Ecosystem assembly logic

_AI: Use this process to assemble the project ecosystem from detected skills:_

```text
for each skill in detected_skills:
    apply skill.structure_map   → merge into STRUCTURE MAP
    apply skill.conventions     → merge into CONVENTIONS
    apply skill.tech_stack      → merge into TECH STACK
    apply skill.dependencies    → merge into DEPENDENCIES
    apply skill.security        → merge into SECURITY
    apply skill.testing         → merge into TESTING STRATEGY
    apply skill.environment     → merge into ENVIRONMENT

after assembly:
    resolve conflicts (two skills defining the same directory)
    remove overwritten defaults
    present assembled ecosystem to user for confirmation
```

### Skill conflict resolution

_AI: When two active skills define overlapping rules:_

| Conflict type | Resolution |
|-------------|-----------|
| Same directory, different rules | Merge rules, flag to user if incompatible |
| Same convention, different format | Use the more specific skill's convention |
| Same dependency, different version | Pin to the higher version, flag for user review |
| Security rules overlap | Combine all — security is additive, never reductive |
| Testing strategy differs | Combine frameworks, separate test directories |

### Manual skill overrides

_AI: If the user mentions a technology not auto-detected, add it here._
_Format: `+skill-name` to add, `-skill-name` to explicitly exclude._

```text
# Example:
# +react
# -database-mongo
```

