### Architecture pattern
_AI: Identify the pattern (MVC, hexagonal, JAMstack, microservices, monolith, etc.). One sentence._

### Enforced directory rules
> These rules are active every session. Violations must be flagged immediately.

| Directory | Owns | Must NOT contain |
|-----------|------|-----------------|
| `config/` | All configuration, env templates | Business logic, UI code |
| `src/controllers/` | Business logic, orchestration | Direct DB queries, UI rendering |
| `src/models/` | Data schemas, DB queries | Business logic, HTTP concerns |
| `src/routes/` | Route definitions, middleware wiring | Business logic (delegate to controllers) |
| `src/services/` | External API calls, shared utilities | Route or controller logic |
| `src/middleware/` | Auth, validation, logging, error handling | Business logic |
| `src/views/` | Templates, components, pages | Inline styles, inline scripts, logic |
| `public/css/` | All stylesheets | JavaScript, server logic |
| `public/js/` | Client-side scripts only | Server logic, direct DB access |
| `public/assets/` | Images, fonts, icons | Code of any kind |
| `tests/unit/` | Unit tests mirroring `src/` structure | Integration concerns |
| `tests/integration/` | Full-flow tests | Unit-level mocks |

_AI: Adapt this table to the actual project stack. Add rows for project-specific directories. Remove rows for layers that don't exist._

