## 📐 CONVENTIONS

> **AI: These are active from day one. Enforce them in every line of code written this session.**

### File naming
| Asset type | Convention | Example |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| Controllers | `camelCase.controller.js` | `userAuth.controller.js` |
| Models | `PascalCase.model.js` | `UserProfile.model.js` |
| Views / templates | `kebab-case.view.html` | `user-dashboard.view.html` |
| CSS files | `kebab-case.css` | `nav-header.css` |
| Client-side JS | `camelCase.js` | `formValidation.js` |
| Config files | `domain.config.js` | `db.config.js` |
| Test files | `[mirrors-src].test.js` | `userAuth.controller.test.js` |
| Services | `camelCase.service.js` | `emailNotification.service.js` |

_AI: Adapt to the actual project stack. For non-JS projects, replace with equivalent conventions._

### CSS rules
- All CSS variables in `public/css/base/variables.css`. No magic color values anywhere else.
- BEM methodology: `.block__element--modifier`. No exceptions.
- No inline styles in HTML/templates. No `style=""` attributes.
- No `!important` unless it is a documented last resort with a comment explaining why.
- Mobile-first: base styles for mobile, `@media (min-width: …)` for larger screens.
- No styles in JavaScript files. Use class toggling instead.

### JavaScript rules
- `const` by default. `let` only when reassignment is required. Never `var`.
- Named exports over default exports.
- `async/await` over `.then()` chains.
- No callback hell. Max 2 levels of nesting in async code.
- No `any` type (TypeScript). Explicit types always.
- No magic numbers or magic strings. Extract to named constants.

### Git
- Branch format: `feature/short-description` · `fix/short-description` · `chore/short-description`
- Commit format: `type(scope): description` — e.g. `feat(auth): add JWT refresh logic`
- No direct commits to `main` or `master`.
- PR required for any change that touches more than one module.

### Comments policy
- No comments that explain WHAT the code does. Names do that.
- Comments only for WHY: hidden constraint, workaround for a specific bug, non-obvious invariant.
- No TODO comments in committed code — open a Backlog item here instead.
- No commented-out code. Delete it; git has the history.

